I was craving Menudo, and it also happened to be a Sunday and I figured let’s give this place a try. My husband got a pozole verde and well, I got menudo. I personally felt it needed a lot more flavor to make it appealing to me. It was definitely not the worst I’ve ever had but meh! It sure tasted like a watered down soup 😫  I really liked that they were real quick to have it ready for me (I had ordered over phone and chose pickup). They have no personal parking so we just pulled to the side next to a parked car, in front of the place. Inside looks decent for a place that’s that small. It does look a little run down but hey, from where I come from (Mexico), they say the best food is within the ugliest places. Not necessarily in every one’s case but still a place to give it a try for yourself. Might give it another try in a year or 2. But for the time being, it’ll be a pass for me.

**BEWARE** This place will try to add any type of surcharge possible. When my husband and I arrived, we got asked if we wanted chips and salsa, of course we said yes assuming they would be free just like any other restaurant right? WRONG. Although it was only $1 I didn't care about the price, but AT LEAST MENTION THAT YOU ARE GOING TO CHARGE! Also, be careful HOW you ordered, they will not be specific with you about anything and charge every little thing you think will be included in your order. Any left overs?? They will charge you for bagging without even mentioning it too!! I was mad when I saw the bill, we added up what we had ordered but it didn't amount to the final bill. There was a bunch of MISCELLANEOUS charges. Although the price difference was like $5, I didn't think it was right to do what they did. WILL NEVER GO BACK TO THIS PLACE AGAIN!! NOW I UNDERSTAND WHY THEY LOST CLIENTELE WHEN IT WOULD BE SO PACKED LIKE 10+ YEARS AGO... Food is not worth the hassle of the mysterious charges.
